everything down!

1211
01:16:33,087 --> 01:16:35,578
Let's restart
those generators.
Where's Will?

1212
01:16:35,656 --> 01:16:38,147
C'mon get me
voice-comm back
as soon as possible.

1213
01:16:38,226 --> 01:16:39,318
You got it.

1214
01:16:41,629 --> 01:16:43,563
Right, let's
load this sucker.

1215
01:16:51,806 --> 01:16:52,966
Hold on!

1216
01:16:57,779 --> 01:16:59,041
John!

1217
01:16:59,113 --> 01:17:01,138
Hang on!
Rachel? What
the hell is that?

1218
01:17:11,859 --> 01:17:14,987
You okay back
there, John?

1219
01:17:15,062 --> 01:17:16,461
Yeah, I'm fine.

1220
01:17:23,337 --> 01:17:27,068
Control. This is
Shuttle Perseus.
Do you read?

1221
01:17:27,141 --> 01:17:31,009
Get those back up
generators online now!

1222
01:17:31,078 --> 01:17:32,875
Tell the President

1223
01:17:32,947 --> 01:17:34,574
they're about
to deploy
the MEG.

1224
01:17:34,649 --> 01:17:36,446
All right,
here we go.

1225
01:17:46,727 --> 01:17:50,026
Okay.
We're locked
and loaded.

1226
01:17:50,097 --> 01:17:53,726
Come on.
Don't do
this to me.

1227
01:17:53,801 --> 01:17:56,599
Control, this is
Shuttle Perseus,
do you read?

1228
01:17:56,671 --> 01:18:00,232
Albert?
Albert!

1229
01:18:00,308 --> 01:18:02,799
John? We lost
all communication.

1230
01:18:02,877 --> 01:18:04,640
Well, get 'em back
for me now.

1231
01:18:04,712 --> 01:18:07,306
I can't!
The problem's
in Houston.

1232
01:18:07,381 --> 01:18:08,643
What happens now?

1233
01:18:08,716 --> 01:18:10,445
Jettison the engines.
We detonate en route

1234
01:18:10,518 --> 01:18:12,543
according to
your calculations.

1235
01:18:12,620 --> 01:18:14,485
Copy that.

1236
01:18:19,927 --> 01:18:21,121
All right.

1237
01:18:21,195 --> 01:18:22,719
The MEG is
set to go.

1238
01:18:22,797 --> 01:18:24,856
I can calculate
detonation timing
on the fly.

1239
01:18:24,932 --> 01:18:27,560
Copy that.
Release those suckers.

1240
01:18:27,635 --> 01:18:29,193
We gotta get
the hell
outta here.

1241
01:18:29,270 --> 01:18:30,168
Got it.

1242
01:18:38,479 --> 01:18:41,380
Shuttle Perseus?
Can you read me? Over.

1243
01:18:41,449 --> 01:18:43,974
Shuttle Perseus?
Do you read?
Over.

1244
01:19:04,472 --> 01:19:05,496
Here we go.

1245
01:19:10,511 --> 01:19:14,504
Shuttle Perseus,
can you read me? Over.

1246
01:19:31,032 --> 01:19:33,057
Rima fault has
hit the critical.

1247
01:19:33,134 --> 01:19:36,695
Repeat. Rima fault
has hit the critical.

1248
01:19:36,771 --> 01:19:39,069
Oh my God.

1249
01:19:39,140 --> 01:19:41,472
We are recording
massive seismic

1250
01:19:41,542 --> 01:19:43,601
disturbances and
rapid growth
in Rima Fault.

1251
01:19:53,754 --> 01:19:55,278
John. If you
can hear me.

1252
01:19:55,356 --> 01:19:56,823
You've got
to detonate.

1253
01:20:08,469 --> 01:20:09,959
Get out of
there John.

1254
01:20:15,042 --> 01:20:16,839
He's coming apart.

1255
01:20:23,084 --> 01:20:23,846
Hold on.

1256
01:20:35,930 --> 01:20:36,954
What are you
waiting for?

1257
01:20:37,031 --> 01:20:38,362
I gotta wait
for a surge

1258
01:20:38,432 --> 01:20:40,127
in magnetic density
within the fault.

1259
01:20:40,201 --> 01:20:42,101
We are
recording ongoing

1260
01:20:42,169 --> 01:20:43,693
and accelerating
seismic activity.

1261
01:20:43,771 --> 01:20:45,671
Blow the damn thing!

1262
01:20:45,740 --> 01:20:47,435
It's too late.

1263
01:20:55,883 --> 01:20:56,713
There it is!

1264
01:21:08,429 --> 01:21:09,589
Hold on.

1265
01:21:15,803 --> 01:21:17,862
We have
a MEG detonation.

1266
01:21:17,938 --> 01:21:20,736
We are picking up
a magnetic spike
and MEG detonation!

1267
01:21:28,049 --> 01:21:30,711
Magnetic amplification
of Rima Fault
has peaked.

1268
01:21:37,324 --> 01:21:41,260
We have continuing
seismic activity
in the fault zone.

1269
01:21:50,838 --> 01:21:53,204
The fault index
is dropping.

1270
01:21:53,274 --> 01:21:54,764
It's stabilizing.

1271
01:21:59,580 --> 01:22:02,344
Radar imaging shows
Rima Fault is closing.

1272
01:22:03,818 --> 01:22:06,343
It's working.
It's working!

1273
01:22:06,420 --> 01:22:10,857
The lunar orbit
is stabilizing.

1274
01:22:10,925 --> 01:22:13,689
Repeat, the lunar orbit
is self-correcting.

1275
01:22:15,963 --> 01:22:18,329
Shuttle Perseus,
do you read me?

1276
01:22:21,168 --> 01:22:23,762
Shuttle Perseus,
can you read
me, over?

1277
01:22:23,838 --> 01:22:28,798
Shuttle Perseus,
this is mission control
do you read, over?

1278
01:22:32,613 --> 01:22:36,310
Shuttle Perseus,
can you read me,
over?

1279
01:22:36,383 --> 01:22:39,443
Shuttle Perseus,
this is mission control.
Do you read, over?

1280
01:22:39,520 --> 01:22:42,284
Shuttle Perseus.
Can you read me?

1281
01:22:43,491 --> 01:22:44,822
This is Shuttle Perseus.

1282
01:22:47,194 --> 01:22:48,821
We're coming home.

1283
01:23:11,752 --> 01:23:15,654
Thank you all.
Good work.
Great job.

1284
01:23:15,723 --> 01:23:18,453
The Perseus Shuttle
mission has succeeded!

1285
01:23:18,526 --> 01:23:22,519
ASI just announced
that the lunar orbit
is returning to normal

1286
01:23:22,596 --> 01:23:26,692
and that Earth, its tidal
and weather systems
have averted disaster.

1287
01:24:09,176 --> 01:24:10,302
You finish it?

1288
01:24:10,377 --> 01:24:12,504
Just now.

1289
01:24:12,580 --> 01:24:15,242
Well, then this
will be right
on time.

1290
01:24:18,686 --> 01:24:20,449
It's the foreword
that victor wrote.

1291
01:24:20,521 --> 01:24:24,013
A foreword?
Should l
be concerned?

1292
01:24:24,091 --> 01:24:26,855
No, it's actually
not too bad.

1293
01:24:26,927 --> 01:24:29,521
He apologized
for everything
he said about your dad

1294
01:24:29,597 --> 01:24:31,189
and he even
gives you
a compliment.

1295
01:24:31,265 --> 01:24:35,634
In his own kinda sorta
arrogant victor way.

1296
01:24:35,703 --> 01:24:37,796
That must have
been humbling.

1297
01:24:37,872 --> 01:24:40,932
So it's basically
seven days a week, 365.

1298
01:24:41,008 --> 01:24:42,976
So when do you
have time to go out?

1299
01:24:43,043 --> 01:24:45,238
Like off campus
kinda stuff?

1300
01:24:45,312 --> 01:24:46,210
Off campus?

1301
01:24:46,280 --> 01:24:47,907
How are
we looking?

1302
01:24:47,982 --> 01:24:51,042
Beautiful. The movers
are bringing in
everything as we speak.

1303
01:24:51,118 --> 01:24:53,382
Lana, the offices are huge.
It's gonna be awesome!

1304
01:24:53,454 --> 01:24:55,251
Offices?

1305
01:24:55,322 --> 01:25:00,453
Garth wants me back.
And I want to be back.
This is where I belong.

1306
01:25:00,527 --> 01:25:02,290
Speaking of where
people belong,

1307
01:25:02,363 --> 01:25:03,853
are you ever planning
to come back to work?

1308
01:25:03,931 --> 01:25:10,302
I've been thinking
about that whole thing.
Excuse me.

1309
01:25:16,944 --> 01:25:21,677
And you've been right.
All along about this whole
taking more time off thing.

1310
01:25:21,749 --> 01:25:25,378
I'm just gonna start
switching over the addresses

1311
01:25:25,452 --> 01:25:30,685
and of course lnternet,
because you can't live
without the lnternet.

1312
01:25:30,758 --> 01:25:32,055
He's just like
you this one.

1313
01:25:32,126 --> 01:25:35,823
Work, work, work.
Damn overachievers.

1314
01:25:35,896 --> 01:25:37,227
Where are you
taking me?

1315
01:25:37,298 --> 01:25:39,732
T o engage
in some off
campus debauchery.

1316
01:25:41,568 --> 01:25:42,967
You know what?

1317
01:25:43,037 --> 01:25:44,698
What?

1318
01:25:44,772 --> 01:25:46,000
He's in trouble.

1319
01:25:50,577 --> 01:25:52,511
So if you're not gonna
go back to work

1320
01:25:52,579 --> 01:25:54,069
right away, what are
you gonna do?

1321
01:25:54,148 --> 01:25:56,173
Think I'll heed
some advice

1322
01:25:56,250 --> 01:25:59,242
about a vacation
I'm in desperate
need of.

1323
01:25:59,320 --> 01:26:02,687
They say space
is the next vacation
hot spot.

1324
01:26:02,756 --> 01:26:05,054
Already been there.

1325
01:26:05,125 --> 01:26:07,685
Do you like sailing?

1326
01:26:07,761 --> 01:26:10,195
Is that
an invitation?

1327
01:26:10,264 --> 01:26:13,165
Yes.
You accepting?

1328
01:26:13,233 --> 01:26:15,258
Uhhh, yes.

1329
01:26:15,336 --> 01:26:16,860
Caribbean?

1330
